                1 0 11-2 0v-1a1 1 0 011-1 1 1 0 100-2zm0 8a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>How do I create an account on the CCH Car Rental web app?</span>
                <svg data-accordion-icon class="w-6 h-6 rotate-180 shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
            </button>
        </h2>
        <div id="accordion-open-body-1" class="hidden" aria-labelledby="accordion-open-heading-1">
            <div class="p-5 font-normal border border-b-0 border-gray-200 max-h-56 overflow-auto">
                <p class=" text-gray-600 font-semibold mb-4">If you are a renter:</p>
                <ul class="pl-5 text-gray-600 list-disc">
                    <li>Go to the homepage of the web app.</li>
                    <li>Look for the "login" button at the right top corner of the page if you already have an account or "sign up" button if you don’t have an account yet.</li>
                    <li>Click on the "sign up" button if you don’t have an account yet.</li>
                    <li>Fill out the registration form with the required information such as your name, email address, birthday, contact number, address, and password.</li>
                    <li>After filling out the form, click the "submit" button at the bottom of the page.</li>
                    <li>Check your email inbox for a verification email from the web app. Click the verification link in the email to confirm your account.</li>
                    <li>After verifying your account, return to the home page of our web app.</li>
                    <li>Click on the "login" button at the right top corner of the page.</li>
                    <li>Enter your email address and password that you provided during registration.</li>
                    <li>Click the "submit" button to proceed and access our web app.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class=" text-gray-600 font-semibold my-4">If you are a car rental owner:</p>
                <ul class="pl-5 text-gray-600 list-disc">
                    <li>Go to the homepage of the web app.</li>
                    <li>Scroll down the page until you see a "become a car rental owner" button on the right side of the page.</li>
                    <li>Click on the "become a car rental owner" button.</li>
                    <li>You will be prompted to "log in/sign up your account".</li>
                    <li>If you already have an account, click on the "log in" button, and enter your email address and password.</li>
                    <li>Click the “submit” button.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class=" text-gray-600 font-semibold my-4">If you don't have an account yet:</p>
                <ul class="pl-5 text-gray-600 list-disc">
                    <li>Click on the "sign up" button.</li>
                    <li>Fill out the registration form with the required information such as your name, email address, birthday, contact number, address, password, picture of your driver’s license, and a valid ID.</li>
                    <li>After filling out the form, click the "submit" button at the bottom of the page.</li>
                    <li>Check your email inbox for a verification email from the web app then click the verification link in the email to confirm your account.</li>
                    <li>Wait for the web app’s admin to verify your account.</li>
                    <li>If your account has already been verified by the web app’s admin, click on the "become a car rental owner" button again.</li>
                    <li>You will be prompted to log in to your account.</li>
                    <li>Enter your email address and password to log in.</li>
                    <li>After logging in, fill out the provided information to become a car rental owner on our web app.</li>
                </ul>
                
            </div>
        </div>

